WEBVTT

00:00.318 --> 00:01.818
<i>My name is Michael Westen.</i>
<i>I used to be a spy until...</i>

00:04.428 --> 00:06.795
We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.

00:07.621 --> 00:09.902
<i>When you're burned,</i>
<i>you've got nothing --</i>

00:09.903 --> 00:12.537
<i>no cash, no credit,</i>
<i>no job history.</i>

00:12.539 --> 00:14.906
<i>You're stuck in whatever city</i>
<i>they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:14.908 --> 00:16.641
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:16.643 --> 00:19.711
<i>You do whatever work</i>
<i>comes your way.</i>

00:19.713 --> 00:22.914
<i>You rely on anyone</i>
<i>who's still talking to you.</i>

00:22.916 --> 00:24.182
<i>A trigger-happy</i>
<i>ex-girlfriend...</i>

00:24.184 --> 00:25.851
Should we shoot them?

00:25.853 --> 00:28.720
<i>...An old friend who used</i>
<i>to inform on you to the FBI...</i>

00:28.722 --> 00:31.089
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.091 --> 00:33.525
<i>...Family, too...</i>
<i>Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:33.527 --> 00:35.727
<i>...If you're desperate.</i>
<i>Someone needs your help, Michael.</i>

00:35.729 --> 00:40.165
<i>Bottom line --</i>
<i>as long as you're burned,</i>

00:44.937 --> 00:48.206
<i>Mysterious trips</i>
<i>around the world with Max.</i>

00:48.208 --> 00:49.841
I mean, he's, what,
your keeper or whatever?

00:49.843 --> 00:52.310
He's my agency contact.

00:54.447 --> 00:55.781
You've been putting up
some W's lately.

00:55.783 --> 00:57.149
The right people are starting
to take notice.

00:57.151 --> 01:00.418
Michael Westen, soon-to-be
reinstated agent of the CIA.

01:00.420 --> 01:01.686
How does that sound?

01:01.688 --> 01:03.789
That sounds great, Max.
Thanks for everything.

01:06.459 --> 01:07.559
Max!

01:09.196 --> 01:11.196
Stay with me.
Stay with me, Max.

01:11.198 --> 01:12.230
Max.

01:16.036 --> 01:19.204
Fi, someone shot Max,
the police are on the way,

01:19.206 --> 01:20.839
and I think I'm holding
the murder weapon.

01:20.841 --> 01:22.507
I covered my tracks...

01:25.211 --> 01:26.778
...So I covered the tracks
of the killer.

01:26.780 --> 01:28.413
Michael, we have to do something
about that gun.

01:28.415 --> 01:30.549
And we need to get an alibi
for you, like, right now.

01:31.818 --> 01:32.918
Let's go to work.

01:36.722 --> 01:38.523
<i>As a spy,</i>

01:38.525 --> 01:40.725
<i>you're in the information</i>
<i>business --</i>

01:40.727 --> 01:42.761
<i>stealing it, protecting it,</i>

01:42.763 --> 01:45.163
<i>and, if you have to,</i>
<i>destroying it.</i>

01:45.165 --> 01:46.731
<i>Some secrets are so dangerous</i>

01:46.733 --> 01:49.367
<i>that you can't allow them</i>
<i>to continue to exist.</i>

01:49.369 --> 01:51.503
<i>A murder weapon</i>
<i>that implicates you</i>

01:51.505 --> 01:53.471
<i>in a crime you didn't commit,</i>
<i>for example,</i>

01:53.473 --> 01:55.640
<i>is a secret best kept</i>

01:55.642 --> 01:58.410
<i>with 4,000 degrees</i>
<i>of burning thermite.</i>

01:58.412 --> 02:00.111
Hey. Got here
as soon as I could.

02:00.113 --> 02:01.713
How'd it go?
Okay.

02:01.715 --> 02:03.215
I put together
some credit-card receipts

02:03.217 --> 02:05.483
putting everyone in Key West
yesterday on a little vacation.

02:05.485 --> 02:07.485
Key West?
Hey.

02:07.487 --> 02:09.354
You want an alibi on such short notice,
you don't get to be picky.

02:11.725 --> 02:12.891
You guys
are melting down a gun.

02:12.893 --> 02:14.092
I don't have
much choice.

02:14.094 --> 02:15.994
Whoever did this knew exactly
what they were doing.

02:15.996 --> 02:18.830
They managed to put a murder weapon
in Michael's hands and get away clean.

02:18.832 --> 02:20.866
I just want to put this out there.
If we go to the cops now --

02:20.868 --> 02:23.301
No. It's not gonna fly.
I talked to the cops.

02:23.303 --> 02:24.736
The CIA has taken over
the scene.

02:24.738 --> 02:26.471
They got a case officer
down here now.

02:26.473 --> 02:28.173
And she wants me in
for a chat.

02:28.175 --> 02:30.041
Oh. Great. Perfect.

02:30.043 --> 02:31.710
And you have no idea
who killed Max?

02:31.712 --> 02:33.311
None. Could be an enemy
of Max's

02:33.313 --> 02:35.180
who wants a burned spy
for a fall guy

02:35.182 --> 02:37.182
or an enemy of mine looking
to keep me out of the game.

02:37.184 --> 02:38.717
What about the people
who burned you?

02:38.719 --> 02:40.752
You said you had doubts
about that investigation.

02:40.754 --> 02:43.021
Anything's possible, but I'm not
gonna be able to find out

02:43.023 --> 02:44.789
if I'm in jail
for first-degree murder.

02:44.791 --> 02:46.524
- We have to get rid of the gun.
- Are you sure about this?

02:46.526 --> 02:48.960
Once you start a cover-up,
there's no going back.

02:48.962 --> 02:50.829
It's already started.
I trashed the key logs

02:50.831 --> 02:52.731
at the murder scene
and wiped the place down.

02:52.733 --> 02:54.532
The only thing
that's gonna save me

02:54.534 --> 02:55.800
is finding
the real killer.

02:55.802 --> 02:57.202
This train's rolling,
brother.

02:57.204 --> 02:59.104
The only question
is whether you get on board.

02:59.106 --> 03:01.806
Hell yeah.
I'm on board. Yeah.

